Quinctius Hirpinus, apparently the friend to whom Epist. 1, 16 is addressed, is not further known. He seems to have been ambitious for wealth, but not averse to pleasures. The date of composition is proba- bly fixed as 26-25 B.c. by the mention of the bellicosus Cantaber v. 1.
